'''艾伦·麦克法兰'''（{{lang-en|Alan Donald James Macfarlane}}, {{bd|1941年|12月20日||}}）是一位英国人类学家和历史学家。<ref>[http://www.alanmacfarlane.com/FILES/allbooks.html Authored and Edited Books] {{Wayback|url=http://www.alanmacfarlane.com/FILES/allbooks.html |date=20170722060626 }} on Alan Macfarlane's personal website</ref>[[皇家历史学会|皇家历史学会]]、人类学会会士。

==生平==
1941年出生于[[英属印度|英属印度]]的一个英国茶种植园的家庭，毕业于[[龙学校|龙学校]]，1963年毕业于[[牛津大学伍斯特学院|牛津大学伍斯特学院]]，1967年凭借论文'[https://ora.ox.ac.uk/objects/uuid:1ffd2745-1cc7-4058-a781-5161cfd3866c ''Witchcraft prosecutions in Essex, 1560–1680: A Sociological Analysis''] {{Wayback|url=https://ora.ox.ac.uk/objects/uuid:1ffd2745-1cc7-4058-a781-5161cfd3866c |date=20160304023432 }}'获得哲学博士，1968年凭借论文'The regulation of marital and sexual relationships in 17th century England'获得[[伦敦政治经济学院|伦敦政治经济学院]]人类学硕士学位，1972年凭借论文'Population and resources in central Nepal'获得[[伦敦大学亚非学院|伦敦大学亚非学院]]博士学位。<ref>Snell, 1989</ref>之后任职于[[剑桥大学国王学院|剑桥大学国王学院]]，1991年升任为正教授，2009年成为终身荣誉教授。<ref>The important Japanese demographer [[Akira_Hayami|Akira Hayami]] celebrated the book: ''"Before reading your book, I had thought that the best understanding of Japan was to be found in the final pages on Japan in Fernand Braudel's 'Grammaire des Civilisations' (1987). But just twenty years later, unlike him, you came and lived in Japan several times. Although his name will be left on my list of the academic studies of Japan, I will certainly put your book first."''</ref>

